Package com.teamten.chess

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Board
    Represents a chess board and the pieces on it.
    ComputerPlayer
    Plays chess.
    ComputerPlayer.EvaluatedMove
    Stores a move and its score.
    Game
    Records an entire game.
    Match
    Plays two versions of our chess program against one another.
    Move
    Stores a move in a chess game and its inverse.
    Piece
    Represents a piece of a type and color.
    PieceType
    Represents a type of piece, such as a queen or rook, but not of a particular color.
    Side
    Sides are represented as an integer, with 0 for white and 1 for black.
    UciParser
    Parses the Universal Chess Interface (UCI) protocol.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IllegalMoveException
    Thrown when a user tries to make a move that's not valid or legal.
